" The mine-workings lie north of the town, " said Dan. " If we head west we ought to cut the trail leading from Gilburg to the north. " So we swung west, making slow going over rough country, sliding on shale, climbing down into draws, circling a big mesa by a four or five mile valley, sandy-floored. It got hotter as the day wore on and we rested gratefully by a small creek where we watered the horses and drank enough to cure our thirst.